I believe you can customize a few more things such as the size of icons when you view folders and such, but I doubt there is a simple quick solution to make one resolution simulate another... Because, you know, if you want a certain resolution you should use that instead of having another one simulate it.<br /><br />But of course, we're now in the LCD era where monitors have native resolutions and look like crap when using anything other than it, so I guess there isn't much you can do. Next time try the monitor before you buy it, to make sure you are comfortable with it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Aug 26, 2009 5:33 pm</p><hr />
